![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/9f4cda64-458f-403f-bd63-7a482b515f6f/20240504_013259.jpg)

The Wrestling Observer has reported that Olympic Gold Medalist Gable Steveson has been released from WWE.

Steveson, known for his remarkable achievements in amateur wrestling, including claiming the 2020 Summer Olympic gold medal and being a three-time age-group world champion, made headlines when he transitioned to the world of professional wrestling. However, despite his stellar track record in freestyle wrestling, Steveson's success did not seamlessly transfer to the realm of sports entertainment.

Steveson's failure to acclimate to the WWE environment serves as a reminder of the challenges athletes face when transitioning between sports. The world of professional wrestling demands a unique blend of athleticism, showmanship, and storytelling, qualities that do not always align with those required in amateur wrestling.